1
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:11,633
<i> I want better results,</i>

2
00:00:11,767 --> 00:00:13,067
<i>especially in the case
you're handling, Garcia.</i>

3
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:15,700
<i>We need to find out
who the mastermind is.</i>

4
00:00:15,833 --> 00:00:18,200
<i>Are you ready to do anything
for your family?</i>

5
00:00:18,333 --> 00:00:20,933
<i>Yes, Boss! I'll do anything.
Just tell me, Boss!</i>

6
00:00:21,067 --> 00:00:22,267
<i> Hey, stop!</i>

7
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:23,533
<i> Boss, I have a lot of money.</i>

8
00:00:23,667 --> 00:00:24,900
<i> How much do you need?</i>

9
00:00:25,033 --> 00:00:26,567
<i>I'll make sure that everything
you say,</i>

10
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:28,267
<i>we'll add to our case
against you, okay?</i>

11
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:30,867
<i>These are bank documents.
This is solid evidence.</i>

12
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:33,467
<i>Be thankful this yielded
good results.</i>

13
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:34,867
<i> Our man inside called.</i>

14
00:00:35,033 --> 00:00:37,867
<i>That engineer you planted inside
Station 12, they took the bait.</i>

15
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:39,533
<i>You're cleared
from your ghost projects.</i>

16
00:00:39,667 --> 00:00:43,067
<i>And it won't happen again
because I'll be the one</i>

17
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:46,100
<i>to oversee the public works
of the entire Calabari.</i>

18
00:00:46,233 --> 00:00:47,233
<i> I just want to know</i>

19
00:00:47,367 --> 00:00:50,100
<i>if Matmat was maltreated
when he was young.</i>

20
00:00:50,233 --> 00:00:52,200
<i> He always hurt Matmat.</i>

21
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:53,867
<i>Did you and your husband work
things out?</i>

22
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:57,233
<i>Not since I found out
he was cheating on me.</i>

23
00:00:57,367 --> 00:00:58,633
<i>Does that mean
he has another woman?</i>

24
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:00,067
<i> He has another man!</i>

25
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:02,100
<i>I need to be more careful
next time.</i>

26
00:01:02,233 --> 00:01:04,467
<i> I'll never fail again!</i>

27
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:06,967
<i> Not anymore!</i>

28
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:10,633
<i> Hello, Sir Tonyo?</i>

29
00:01:10,767 --> 00:01:12,400
<i>I know what the killer
looks like!</i>

30
00:01:12,533 --> 00:01:13,700
<i>Are you sure
that's what you saw?</i>

31
00:01:13,833 --> 00:01:15,333
<i> Sir, that's what I saw!</i>

32
00:01:15,467 --> 00:01:16,967
<i> He has no record of murder.</i>

33
00:01:17,100 --> 00:01:18,267
<i> He was imprisoned for robbery.</i>

34
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:20,133
<i>He hasn't been caught
for murder yet, Sir.</i>

35
00:01:20,267 --> 00:01:22,833
<i>But we have a cold case here
where he's the suspect.</i>

36
00:01:22,967 --> 00:01:25,367
<i> But why are his victims gay?</i>

37
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:28,467
<i>Because the father who is
hurting him is a closet gay.</i>

38
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:31,500
<i>Good news because Enriquez has
discovered the serial killer.</i>

39
00:01:31,633 --> 00:01:32,633
<i>We have been looking for
a long time.</i>

40
00:01:32,767 --> 00:01:34,800
<i>And it is none other
than Mateo Ramos.</i>

41
00:01:34,933 --> 00:01:36,933
<i>And to speed up the search
for him,</i>

42
00:01:37,067 --> 00:01:38,700
<i>we are ready to offer a reward.</i>

43
00:01:38,833 --> 00:01:41,267
<i>One million for anyone
who can point out</i>

44
00:01:41,433 --> 00:01:44,100
<i> where Mateo Ramos is hiding.</i>

45
00:01:44,233 --> 00:01:46,967
Many people will call us
as expected.

46
00:01:47,100 --> 00:01:48,367
With each call,

47
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:53,600
we will first verify how legit
the tip is before we act.

48
00:01:53,733 --> 00:01:56,567
If we have a good tip,
tell me immediately.

49
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:57,767
Is that clear?

50
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:58,933
Yes, Sir!

51
00:01:59,067 --> 00:02:00,200
Okay, back to work.

52
00:02:03,467 --> 00:02:07,200
Noble, Paloma, you should
partner up first, okay?

53
00:02:07,333 --> 00:02:08,300
Copy, Sir.

54
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:10,533
Conde, Samson,

55
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:16,667
you should partner up first
and find Mateo Ramos.

56
00:02:16,833 --> 00:02:18,067
Yes, Sir.

57
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:20,633
Okay. Conde, let's talk first.

58
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,733
You take care of it.

59
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:28,233
Bobby!

60
00:02:28,367 --> 00:02:29,867
Did you hear that?

61
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:32,500
Tonyo and I are partners.

62
00:02:32,633 --> 00:02:33,767
So basically,

63
00:02:33,900 --> 00:02:36,400
you were the one who sewed up
the case we were handling.

64
00:02:36,533 --> 00:02:39,933
I feel sad for you.
Are you still doing desk job?

65
00:02:40,067 --> 00:02:42,767
It's your fault.
You're so stubborn.

66
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:48,567
But don't worry,
I'll take care of Tonyo for you.

67
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,033
Charlie.

68
00:02:52,233 --> 00:02:53,367
Stop picking on Enriquez.

69
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:56,133
It's okay, Sir.

70
00:02:56,267 --> 00:02:58,900
Lieutenant Samson might not be
able to sleep

71
00:02:59,033 --> 00:03:00,333
if she doesn't approach me.

72
00:03:01,667 --> 00:03:02,633
I'll go ahead.

73
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:40,700
The Mayor is really good.

74
00:03:40,833 --> 00:03:42,433
That's right, right?

75
00:03:42,567 --> 00:03:47,100
A reward for those who want
to find that gay killer.

76
00:03:47,233 --> 00:03:48,167
Yes, that's right.

77
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:51,867
The problem there, the callers
might fool them.

78
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:54,000
They'll give them different
kinds of tips.

79
00:03:54,167 --> 00:03:55,667
That's their problem.

80
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:57,367
But you know, if it were me,

81
00:03:57,500 --> 00:04:00,467
I'd make sure the tip
I give is right.

82
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:01,800
So the effort isn't wasted.

83
00:04:01,933 --> 00:04:04,533
And besides, Mar,
even if there's no reward,

84
00:04:04,667 --> 00:04:07,167
I want to catch that witch.

85
00:04:08,533 --> 00:04:09,900
What can you say, Captain?

86
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:14,767
That's right.

87
00:04:15,867 --> 00:04:17,700
But I still don't like
that Glen!

88
00:04:21,900 --> 00:04:23,700
You know, she's always been
a real villain, Mar.

89
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:25,000
That's right. You might think
that she was the one running

90
00:04:25,133 --> 00:04:26,933
- for mayor, right?
- That's true.

91
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:29,000
Captain, she thinks...

92
00:04:32,167 --> 00:04:33,167
Come in!

93
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:38,800
Enriquez.

94
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:46,900
I want to talk to you.

95
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,033
First...

96
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:55,133
I want to commend you
for a job well done.

97
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:59,533
I admit that you're good,

98
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:02,300
but often,

99
00:05:02,433 --> 00:05:05,967
you're stubborn and don't know
how to obey.

100
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:10,567
Is that why you won't give me
an assignment, Sir?

101
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:11,800
Yes, Enriquez.

102
00:05:12,867 --> 00:05:14,267
You're still on a desk job,

103
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:17,667
but just continue
what you're doing.

104
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:21,900
Sir, I just want to help
catch Mateo Ramos.

105
00:05:22,033 --> 00:05:23,700
And you already did enough.

106
00:05:25,467 --> 00:05:27,067
Thank you very much, Enriquez.

107
00:05:29,067 --> 00:05:30,133
Yes, Sir.

108
00:05:30,267 --> 00:05:33,667
Go ahead,
get back to your work.

109
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:34,767
Okay Sir.

110
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:38,800
Enriquez.

111
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,433
Just a friendly advice,

112
00:05:42,567 --> 00:05:47,300
admitting you need to rest
is not a weakness.

113
00:06:06,867 --> 00:06:08,567
Hi, Grandmother.

114
00:06:08,733 --> 00:06:10,400
Hi, Grandchild!

115
00:06:17,233 --> 00:06:20,000
Mar and Abdul,
where are they?

116
00:06:20,133 --> 00:06:21,533
They're not yet here.

117
00:06:21,667 --> 00:06:26,333
They're hunting the criminal
because they're so desperate

118
00:06:26,467 --> 00:06:29,267
for the one million
that the Mayor will give.

119
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:32,767
Gosh, those two.

120
00:06:33,900 --> 00:06:34,900
I'll go ahead, Grandmother.

121
00:06:35,033 --> 00:06:37,200
Wait a minute, Grandchild.

122
00:06:37,333 --> 00:06:39,067
Come on, sit down.

123
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:41,000
Let's talk first.

124
00:06:41,167 --> 00:06:42,567
I miss you.

125
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:44,733
Even if it's just for a moment.

126
00:06:50,033 --> 00:06:53,000
You know, I can read your
feelings.

127
00:06:53,133 --> 00:06:56,300
It seems like you're going
through something.

128
00:06:56,433 --> 00:06:58,367
Is it because of Tonyo?

129
00:06:59,900 --> 00:07:01,100
There's a lot, Grandmother.

130
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:04,300
First...

131
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,967
Tonyo and I had an argument.

132
00:07:08,100 --> 00:07:09,100
And then...

133
00:07:11,033 --> 00:07:14,033
it feels like I got demoted.
I'm just doing a desk job.

134
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:19,767
I feel like I haven't done
anything right.

135
00:07:22,767 --> 00:07:27,067
You know, Grandchild,
we're still lucky.

136
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:32,333
Even though we cry,
we're still beautiful.

137
00:07:32,467 --> 00:07:37,067
Problems today,
stories tomorrow.

138
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:41,567
Tears today,
eye bags tomorrow.

139
00:07:41,700 --> 00:07:43,233
Grandmother,
you're something else.

140
00:07:48,933 --> 00:07:50,433
Don't worry, Grandmother.

141
00:07:51,967 --> 00:07:54,367
I can handle all of this.

142
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:59,133
I'm not worried because I know
you can handle it.

143
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:02,700
Because the grandchild
who is beautiful.

144
00:08:02,833 --> 00:08:06,033
Inherited her looks
from her Grandmother.

145
00:08:10,667 --> 00:08:12,000
Thank you, Grandmother.

146
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:15,100
We can handle this.

147
00:08:17,700 --> 00:08:19,500
I'm going to rest.

148
00:08:19,633 --> 00:08:20,533
Good night.

149
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:21,700
Good night.

150
00:08:26,567 --> 00:08:27,767
Good night.

151
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:29,200
Go to sleep, too.

152
00:08:29,333 --> 00:08:30,500
Yes!

153
00:08:48,633 --> 00:08:49,633
Are you sure?

154
00:08:49,767 --> 00:08:51,767
Yes, Ma'am.

155
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:52,933
Conde.

156
00:08:54,967 --> 00:08:56,367
These two had a tip.

157
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:59,233
De Jesus, Torres,
what tip did you get?

158
00:08:59,367 --> 00:09:02,267
Sir, someone from Village Amador
called me.

159
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:03,800
They said they noticed a tenant

160
00:09:03,933 --> 00:09:05,733
who was always wearing a mask.

161
00:09:05,867 --> 00:09:08,333
He just moved here
two weeks ago.

162
00:09:09,967 --> 00:09:12,067
Is there no other verification?

163
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:14,900
Because the leads that
Dizon and Garcia followed,

164
00:09:15,033 --> 00:09:16,300
it's the same thing
and no results.

165
00:09:16,433 --> 00:09:18,733
Sir, I received a call just now.

166
00:09:18,867 --> 00:09:20,867
The caller is also
from Village Amador.

167
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:25,533
He said he saw a man with
a birthmark on his right hand.

168
00:09:25,667 --> 00:09:27,133
What, Conde?

169
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:28,500
Let's check it?

170
00:09:28,633 --> 00:09:29,633
Let's go.

171
00:09:29,767 --> 00:09:31,867
De Jesus, Torres, thank you.

172
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,167
- Okay, Sir.
- Thank you.

173
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:37,633
Morning, Grandmother.

174
00:09:37,767 --> 00:09:39,267
Morning, Grandchild.

175
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,333
What's that?

176
00:09:44,433 --> 00:09:46,867
My text mate, the neighbor.

177
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,000
What's that?

178
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:51,867
Oh my!

179
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,267
Grandmother, you left the rice
on the stove.

180
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:55,633
It's burned.

181
00:09:57,367 --> 00:09:58,300
Oh, my.

182
00:09:58,433 --> 00:10:01,967
Grandmother, you left
the water running too.

183
00:10:02,133 --> 00:10:03,367
<i> Grandmother...</i>

184
00:10:04,400 --> 00:10:05,500
Grandmother!

185
00:10:05,633 --> 00:10:08,567
Do you know
that you're cooking?

186
00:10:08,700 --> 00:10:11,300
Was I cooking?

187
00:10:11,433 --> 00:10:13,167
Yes, and it got burned.

188
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:15,833
Then the faucet,
you left the faucet running.

189
00:10:15,967 --> 00:10:16,967
Faucet?

190
00:10:19,433 --> 00:10:21,800
And Grandmother,
why are you wearing this?

191
00:10:21,933 --> 00:10:24,067
You're not even
getting ready yet.

192
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:25,867
And it's worn the wrong way.

193
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:31,233
There.

194
00:10:32,533 --> 00:10:33,567
Are you okay?

195
00:10:37,567 --> 00:10:39,933
Look at what Captain did
to our food.

196
00:10:40,067 --> 00:10:41,733
It's burnt, right?

197
00:10:41,867 --> 00:10:43,100
The rice is a waste.

198
00:10:43,233 --> 00:10:44,333
That's right.

199
00:10:44,467 --> 00:10:47,067
Even the faucet
wasn't turned off.

200
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:49,600
The water bill is so expensive
these days!

201
00:10:49,733 --> 00:10:53,000
If I see Captain,
I'll definitely tell her.

202
00:10:55,433 --> 00:10:57,533
- Hot. Yes.
- Hot? Take it easy, friend.

203
00:10:59,233 --> 00:11:00,900
- Oh, Bobby.
- Bobby.

204
00:11:01,033 --> 00:11:02,400
How's Captain?

205
00:11:02,533 --> 00:11:04,667
There, sleeping, resting.

206
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:06,767
Maybe she's tired.

207
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:09,600
All she does is work.

208
00:11:09,767 --> 00:11:11,000
She does not want
to ralex anymore.

209
00:11:11,133 --> 00:11:12,833
Just let her be.

210
00:11:12,967 --> 00:11:16,667
Hey, Bobby, is there any news
about Mateo Ramos?

211
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:20,300
We looked for him too,
but there's nothing.

212
00:11:20,433 --> 00:11:22,033
Whoever points out

213
00:11:22,167 --> 00:11:23,400
where that jerk
is will be lucky.

214
00:11:23,533 --> 00:11:25,233
I don't have any news.

215
00:11:25,367 --> 00:11:26,400
Why?

216
00:11:27,700 --> 00:11:28,733
I'm on leave.

217
00:11:28,867 --> 00:11:33,667
What? You took a leave
in the middle of a manhunt?

218
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:38,167
Oh my, what if he victimizes
one of us?

219
00:11:38,300 --> 00:11:39,267
Oh no, that's scary.

220
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:41,000
What if...

221
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:42,800
It's Abdul.

222
00:11:43,967 --> 00:11:45,500
Not me.

223
00:11:45,633 --> 00:11:47,300
That's right.

224
00:11:47,433 --> 00:11:49,500
I have a lot to take care of.

225
00:11:51,500 --> 00:11:52,533
What?

226
00:12:02,733 --> 00:12:04,167
Madam, how are you?

227
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:05,300
You know,

228
00:12:05,433 --> 00:12:08,267
I'm not sure if Mateo Ramos
has been caught yet.

229
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:11,267
But when I identified him
at the police station.

230
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:13,733
You know, all my visions
disappeared.

231
00:12:13,867 --> 00:12:15,633
Oh, thank you.

232
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:18,800
Sometimes, I'm afraid of you,
your vision.

233
00:12:18,933 --> 00:12:20,967
It's like you're possessed.

234
00:12:21,100 --> 00:12:22,200
I'm sorry.

235
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:23,633
I'll make it up to you.

236
00:12:23,767 --> 00:12:25,267
You'll make it up to me, Madam?

237
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:27,000
Just increase my salary.

238
00:12:27,133 --> 00:12:28,467
What if I light you up
just like these?

239
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:29,500
You're really something else.

240
00:12:29,633 --> 00:12:31,700
You know I'm still recovering
from life.

241
00:12:31,833 --> 00:12:34,133
A lot has happened to me.

242
00:12:34,267 --> 00:12:35,667
My goodness.

243
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:38,367
<i> Anyone home?</i>

244
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:42,233
Come on, go down.
Look who it is.

245
00:12:42,367 --> 00:12:43,667
<i> Anyone home?</i>

246
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:50,000
Madam, you have a visitor.

247
00:12:53,367 --> 00:12:54,267
Go ahead.

248
00:12:56,267 --> 00:12:57,300
Thank you.

249
00:12:58,733 --> 00:13:00,133
Alma.

250
00:13:00,267 --> 00:13:01,233
Bobby...

251
00:13:01,367 --> 00:13:04,200
You're the one with Tonyo
at the station, right?

252
00:13:05,900 --> 00:13:06,900
Are you busy?

253
00:13:08,733 --> 00:13:11,533
Is this about Mateo Ramos?

254
00:13:12,767 --> 00:13:13,800
No.

255
00:13:23,167 --> 00:13:24,233
Damn!

256
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:26,967
I need to move again!

257
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:35,467
I really should be further away!

258
00:13:38,700 --> 00:13:42,067
Where no one can see me.

259
00:13:44,333 --> 00:13:46,333
I can do whatever I want...

260
00:13:47,667 --> 00:13:49,433
without anyone noticing.

261
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:59,233
You're really my only ally.

262
00:14:01,233 --> 00:14:03,300
So don't leave me, okay?

263
00:14:03,433 --> 00:14:05,333
Don't forsake me.

264
00:14:05,467 --> 00:14:07,100
We're in the same boat.

265
00:14:22,100 --> 00:14:23,100
That's the one.

266
00:14:24,133 --> 00:14:25,767
There's the house
that we were told about.

267
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:31,633
We have to assume that Mateo
is really inside.

268
00:14:34,467 --> 00:14:36,233
What's our strategy, Tonyo?

269
00:14:42,567 --> 00:14:43,533
Actually,

270
00:14:45,233 --> 00:14:47,267
I wanted to talk to you
even before what happened

271
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:48,567
to Mateo Ramos.

272
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:50,433
Okay, sit here.

273
00:14:50,567 --> 00:14:52,067
Stay here.

274
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,167
Okay.

275
00:14:55,567 --> 00:14:56,900
What's this about?

276
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:00,867
My father just died.

277
00:15:02,233 --> 00:15:04,600
My friends recommended you
to me.

278
00:15:04,733 --> 00:15:08,200
Based on your help
with Mateo's case,

279
00:15:10,100 --> 00:15:12,500
I know you're telling the truth.

280
00:15:12,633 --> 00:15:14,833
Do you want to talk
to your father?

281
00:15:16,767 --> 00:15:18,600
I really want to apologize
to him.

282
00:15:18,733 --> 00:15:20,933
When he found out
I was her daughter,

283
00:15:21,067 --> 00:15:22,900
he wanted me
to call him Father.

284
00:15:24,333 --> 00:15:26,967
But I couldn't give him
that right away.

285
00:15:28,733 --> 00:15:29,767
I don't know.

286
00:15:30,900 --> 00:15:35,300
Maybe it's because I grew up
without a father.

287
00:15:36,633 --> 00:15:39,567
I just got used to grandmother
always being with me,

288
00:15:39,700 --> 00:15:41,000
being there for me.

289
00:15:41,133 --> 00:15:44,600
So I thought I could do
without him.

290
00:15:47,467 --> 00:15:51,433
But when he came into my life,
everything changed.

291
00:15:51,567 --> 00:15:53,067
I was wrong.

292
00:15:54,367 --> 00:15:59,067
There was Bobby inside me
who was so eager for the love

293
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:00,533
and hug of a father.

294
00:16:03,667 --> 00:16:05,833
But he was taken from me
right away.

295
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:09,367
Maybe the universe is saying...

296
00:16:11,733 --> 00:16:13,267
"You're acting like a fool,
Bobby.

297
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:16,567
Your father is already there,
you're making him suffer.

298
00:16:18,733 --> 00:16:21,233
If you don't want him,
I'll take him back from you."

299
00:16:21,367 --> 00:16:24,133
So, the universe took him back.

300
00:16:24,267 --> 00:16:28,400
I thought it was hard
because I didn't have a father,

301
00:16:28,533 --> 00:16:30,700
and I didn't know him...

302
00:16:30,833 --> 00:16:34,500
But it's harder
because I did know him,

303
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:40,200
but I didn't even make him feel
that I needed him.

304
00:16:45,233 --> 00:16:46,200
Sorry.

305
00:16:54,233 --> 00:16:55,933
Close your eyes.

306
00:17:07,067 --> 00:17:08,200
Anybody home?

307
00:17:13,567 --> 00:17:14,833
Anybody home?

308
00:17:27,433 --> 00:17:29,200
Anybody home?

309
00:17:29,333 --> 00:17:32,300
Sir, I'm just conducting
a survey.

310
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:55,067
Mateo Ramos...

311
00:17:56,733 --> 00:17:58,267
Stop, hey!

312
00:18:01,133 --> 00:18:02,533
- Stop!
- Tonyo!

313
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:25,933
That's enough!

314
00:18:26,067 --> 00:18:27,300
You can't escape anymore!

315
00:18:30,167 --> 00:18:31,733
Father!

316
00:18:31,867 --> 00:18:33,067
Father, I'm sorry, Father!

317
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:34,667
I'll be good!

318
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:35,933
I'm sorry!

319
00:18:36,067 --> 00:18:39,533
I'll do everything you say,
Father, just don't hurt me.

320
00:18:39,667 --> 00:18:41,533
Father, I'm sorry, Father.

321
00:18:41,667 --> 00:18:43,200
Don't hurt mother anymore.

322
00:18:43,333 --> 00:18:45,167
Please have mercy!

323
00:18:45,300 --> 00:18:46,733
I'm sorry, Father!

324
00:18:46,867 --> 00:18:50,433
Please have mercy, Father,
don't hurt me, Father.

325
00:18:53,033 --> 00:18:54,700
I can feel him.

326
00:18:59,167 --> 00:19:01,367
Your father isn't mad at you.

327
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:03,100
He understands you.

328
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:06,667
And in fact,

329
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:09,767
he's the one who wants
to apologize to you

330
00:19:09,900 --> 00:19:12,500
during the times
when you needed your father

331
00:19:12,633 --> 00:19:14,133
and he's not there.

332
00:19:14,267 --> 00:19:17,233
Don't think that everyone
you love

333
00:19:17,367 --> 00:19:19,133
is being taken away
from your life.

334
00:19:19,267 --> 00:19:23,333
Your grandmother is still there.

335
00:19:23,467 --> 00:19:30,167
And if you don't understand now,
only God knows.

336
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:34,467
No matter what
you're going through

337
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:36,600
and what you'll go through,

338
00:19:36,733 --> 00:19:40,833
your father wants you to know
that he's there for you.

339
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:49,233
Your father wants you to know
that he's there for you

340
00:19:49,367 --> 00:19:51,500
and that he's hugging you.

341
00:19:54,067 --> 00:19:58,433
He's so happy that
even for a little while,

342
00:19:58,567 --> 00:20:00,733
you considered him your father.

343
00:20:03,533 --> 00:20:05,233
He loves you so much...

344
00:20:06,933 --> 00:20:08,967
and he's so proud of you.

345
00:20:13,733 --> 00:20:16,000
Thank you, Alma.

346
00:20:58,667 --> 00:21:00,533
Sergeant Enriquez!

347
00:21:00,667 --> 00:21:02,433
Mayor, good morning.

348
00:21:02,567 --> 00:21:04,267
Are you going to Station 12?

349
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:05,867
Come on, we'll drop you off.

350
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:07,900
No thanks, Mayor. It's okay.

351
00:21:08,033 --> 00:21:09,033
I'm going to the cemetery.

352
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:10,800
I'm going to visit Father.

353
00:21:10,933 --> 00:21:12,400
You're going to the cemetery.

354
00:21:12,533 --> 00:21:13,500
Come on, come with us.

355
00:21:13,633 --> 00:21:15,133
We're going there too.

356
00:21:15,267 --> 00:21:16,100
Come, come.

357
00:21:18,900 --> 00:21:21,767
- Come with us.
- Glen, what are you doing?

358
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:23,900
That girl won't come with us.

359
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:27,200
- Mom?
- No, Glen.

360
00:21:27,333 --> 00:21:28,367
Isn't it enough

361
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:30,800
that you've been showered with
my family's wealth?

362
00:21:30,933 --> 00:21:33,033
You're being too arrogant.

363
00:21:33,167 --> 00:21:34,733
Mom, please.

364
00:21:34,867 --> 00:21:36,400
Whether she's dad's daughter
or not,

365
00:21:36,533 --> 00:21:37,767
she deserves respect.

366
00:21:39,867 --> 00:21:41,967
Bobby, I'm sorry.

367
00:21:42,133 --> 00:21:44,133
Mayor, it's okay.

368
00:21:44,267 --> 00:21:47,100
I won't go to the cemetery
for now.

369
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:53,167
If you can, maybe you can just
put this on father's grave.

370
00:21:53,300 --> 00:21:54,533
Okay.

371
00:21:54,667 --> 00:21:55,733
No!

372
00:21:55,867 --> 00:21:59,067
I will not bring cheap flowers
to my husband's grave.

373
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:01,200
Mom, please stop it.

374
00:22:01,333 --> 00:22:02,400
That's enough.

375
00:22:04,300 --> 00:22:05,800
Bobby, please forgive me again.

376
00:22:05,933 --> 00:22:07,000
It's okay, Mayor.

377
00:22:08,067 --> 00:22:09,567
- Thank you.
- Okay, okay.

378
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:11,100
- Be careful.
- Be careful, too.

379
00:22:37,233 --> 00:22:39,067
Dude, you and Miss Faye
are getting along.

380
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:40,133
Does the Mayor know that?

381
00:22:40,267 --> 00:22:41,167
She already introduced me.

382
00:22:41,300 --> 00:22:43,500
- Hey!
- Dude, it's okay! You're lucky!

383
00:22:43,633 --> 00:22:44,700
Remember this.

384
00:22:44,833 --> 00:22:48,367
If the police catch you
and you point me out,

385
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:50,167
I'll wipe out your race.

386
00:22:50,333 --> 00:22:51,433
Are you mad?

387
00:22:51,567 --> 00:22:52,567
What do you think?

388
00:22:52,700 --> 00:22:54,800
I am not a fortune teller
like Alma.

389
00:22:54,933 --> 00:22:56,433
Yes, I'm angry with you!

390
00:22:56,567 --> 00:22:57,467
Happy?

391
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:59,967
Maybe you can bridge me
to Tonyo?

392
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:01,233
Didn't you two ever become
a couple?

393
00:23:01,367 --> 00:23:03,100
You really are perfect partners.

394
00:23:03,233 --> 00:23:04,933
Tonyo and I look good together.
